body:
Done.

Please note that the updated [proposal] also specifies that examples with output are treated as tests and printed as

```json
{
  "Package": "foo",
  "Test": {
    "Name": "Example1",
    "Status": "PASS",
    "T": 1000
  }
}
```

`Status` cannot be `"SKIP"`. Never has `Log`.

[proposal]: https://golang.org/design/2981-go-test-json
